				<div class="col-md-2"></div>
			</div>
			<p>I recollect that in the 1980s the Peeliamman Temple was very small—it may have been little more than just an idol below a tree. It has grown much larger since then. Maybe the other two temples too were very small in the pre-IIT days. It was pointed out to me recently that the stone fence-posts of the Vinayakar Temple are of a style not seen anywhere else in the IIT campus. Maybe those posts too predate the institute.</p>
			<p>So much for the oldest surviving structures. What structures have not survived? What constructions were put up before the British period that have disappeared? Did the Cholas or the Pallavas construct anything here? Oh for a time machine that we could take for a spin in the campus!</p>
			<p>We could witness great changes in climate taking place rapidly. We could watch the sea retreat during the Ice Ages and advance in the interim periods. We could view animals that are extinct today. Rocks would be created and destroyed. We would go back to the Big Bang. There would be a singularity!</p>
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
